      • beginClassification

        public IClassificationRun beginClassification(java.lang.String branchPath,
                                              java.lang.String reasonerId,
                                              java.lang.String userId)
        Description copied from interface: ISnomedClassificationService
        Starts a classification run.

        Reasoner identifiers correspond to Equinox fully qualified extension identifiers for the extension point " org.protege.editor.owl.inference_reasonerfactory".

        Specified by:
        beginClassification in interface ISnomedClassificationService
        Parameters:
        branchPath - the branch path to run the classification on (may not be null)
        reasonerId - the identifier of the reasoner factory to use, eg. "org.semanticweb.elk.elk.reasoner.factory" for the ELK reasoner (may not be null)
        userId - the requesting user's identifier to check (may not be null)
        Returns:
        a new IClassificationRun corresponding to the input parameters, as returned by #getClassificationRun(String, String, String, String)

      • getEquivalentConceptSets

        public java.util.List<IEquivalentConceptSet> getEquivalentConceptSets(java.lang.String branchPath,
                                                                      java.lang.String classificationId,
                                                                      java.util.List<ExtendedLocale> locales,
                                                                      java.lang.String userId)
        Description copied from interface: ISnomedClassificationService
        Retrieves the list of equivalent concept sets found during classification. Concepts in an equivalence set were considered equivalent by the reasoner based on their defining properties.

        Results are only available if the status of this run is set to COMPLETED.

        Specified by:
        getEquivalentConceptSets in interface ISnomedClassificationService
        Parameters:
        branchPath - the branch path to match (may not be null)
        classificationId - the classification identifier to match (may not be null)
        locales - the list of locales to use, in order of preference
        userId - the requesting user's identifier to match (may not be null)
        Returns:
        a list of equivalent concept sets, or an empty list if no such concept set exists

      • getRelationshipChanges

        public IRelationshipChangeList getRelationshipChanges(java.lang.String branchPath,
                                                      java.lang.String classificationId,
                                                      java.lang.String userId,
                                                      int offset,
                                                      int limit)
        Description copied from interface: ISnomedClassificationService
        Retrieves the pageable list of suggested relationship changes found during classification.

        Suggestions include inactivation of existing relationships as well as creation of new relationships to ensure that the terminology's IS A relationships reflect the state inferred by the reasoner, and the entire terminology is kept in distribution normal form at the same time.

        Changes are only available if the status of this run is set to COMPLETED.

        Specified by:
        getRelationshipChanges in interface ISnomedClassificationService
        Parameters:
        branchPath - the branch path to match (may not be null)
        classificationId - the classification identifier to match (may not be null)
        userId - the requesting user's identifier to match (may not be null)
        offset - the starting offset in the list (may not be negative)
        limit - the maximum number of results to return (may not be negative)
        Returns:
        a list of suggested relationship changes, or an empty list if no such suggestions exist

      • persistChanges

        public void persistChanges(java.lang.String branchPath,
                           java.lang.String classificationId,
                           java.lang.String userId)
        Description copied from interface: ISnomedClassificationService
        Persists suggested changes for the specified classification run to the terminology store.

        Saving is only possible if the status of this run is set to COMPLETED.

        This method returns immediately. The process can be followed by polling the ClassificationStatus of the classification run using #getClassificationRun(String, String, String, String).

        Specified by:
        persistChanges in interface ISnomedClassificationService
        Parameters:
        branchPath - the branch path to match (may not be null)
        classificationId - the classification identifier to match (may not be null)
        userId - the requesting user's identifier to match (may not be null)
